2) General Administration Department Notification No. SRV-2021 /
Government Orders: -

As per the provisions of Section 4 (4) and 4 (5) of the Maharashtra Prevention of Delay in discharge of Government Duties and Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees Act, 2005, the following officers of the Sub-Divisional Magistrate cadre shall, for administrative reasons / on request, be posted in front of their name in column No. The post indicated in section 4 is being posted with the approval of the competent authority in the interest of public service and administrative convenience.

The aforesaid Deputy Collector is being unilaterally relieved from his present office with effect from the date 25.02.2025 (M.No.) for joining the post of Secretary. The officer concerned should immediately submit the report of appointment to the Government by e-mail / post at e2.revenue@maharashtra.gov.in.

3. The officers concerned shall be liable to disciplinary action under the provisions of the Representation of the People Act, 1950 and the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct of Business) Rules, 1979, if they are found not to have joined the place of transfer before the expiry of the period of office, in accordance with the said provisions prescribed under Rule 15 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption, non-acceptance of service and Provisions during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981.

The Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption of office, non-recurring service and remuneration during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981, relating to the period prescribed under the rules.
